wikipedia_page.main: John Arthur Eyton-Jones  (25 September 1862 – 3 March 1940) was a Welsh international footballer. He was part of the Wales national football team between 1883 and 1884, playing 4 matches and scoring 1 goal. He played his first match on 17 March 1883 against Ireland and his last match on 29 March 1884 against Scotland.
